Today, log4j does not support defered logging, ie. we have to put the cat.debug
() statement in the method calling the debugger, for example:

class SampleClass{

void test(){
 log("blabla");
}

void log(String s){
 cat.debug(s);
}
}
will print a debug statement like:
Sample class 8: blabla

But we wanted to have
Sample Class 4: blabla

this could be done using a method like
cat.debug("blabla",1) meaning, one-level deferentiation.

I saw log4 implementation, it uses the StatckTrace to find the line number of 
the calling method. It would just need to take a given of line down to have 
another method call.

Feel free to contact me for more information.

Reshad Moussa
